docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — An Internal Revenue Service whistle-blower filed a complaint alleging that senior Treasury officials tried to exert influence over the mandatory audit of President Trump’s tax returns, according to a person familiar with the matter.

headline.print_headline: Treasury Officials Implicated in I.R.S. Whistle-Blower Report Over President’s Taxes

docs.abstract: Protesters shut down a speech by Kevin K. McAleenan, the latest effort by opponents of the Trump administration’s hard-line immigration policies to let their grievances be known to policymakers.
docs.snippet: Protesters shut down a speech by Kevin K. McAleenan, the latest effort by opponents of the Trump administration’s hard-line immigration policies to let their grievances be known to policymakers.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Kevin K. McAleenan, the acting secretary of homeland security, was forced offstage at Georgetown University’s law school by demonstrators who shut down his planned keynote address as they protested the Trump administration’s immigration policies.

headline.main: Acting Homeland Security Chief Shouted Off Stage at Georgetown Law
headline.print_headline: Homeland Security Chief Shouted Off Stage by Immigration Protesters

docs.abstract: The operation will focus on undocumented migrants in at least 10 major cities across the country and who had their cases expedited and were served deportation orders.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Immigration and Customs Enforcement is expected to send agents into communities on Sunday morning to begin a coordinated operation deporting undocumented immigrant family members across the country, according to two Department of Homeland Security officials.

headline.print_headline: Operation in Place to Round Up More Than 2,000 for Deportation

docs.abstract: The move is the administration’s latest step to respond to a surge of undocumented immigrants and asylum seekers trying to enter the United States.
docs.snippet: The move is the administration’s latest step to respond to a surge of undocumented immigrants and asylum seekers trying to enter the United States.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Pentagon said on Wednesday that it would build temporary housing along the southwestern border for 7,500 migrant adults facing deportation, the latest step in the administration’s efforts to respond to a surge of undocumented immigrants and asylum seekers trying to enter the United States.

headline.main: Pentagon to Build Temporary Shelter for 7,500 Migrant Adults Facing Deportation

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The union representing the nation’s immigration judges filed two labor complaints against the Justice Department on Friday, escalating a fight between the Trump administration and those who play a central role in the White House’s attempt to limit immigration to the United States.

headline.print_headline: Union for Immigration Judges Lodges Complaints Against the Justice Department

docs.abstract: During trade talks, U.S. officials have avoided confronting China about its persecution of Uighurs despite bipartisan pressure, fearing such a move could harm a deal.
docs.snippet: During trade talks, U.S. officials have avoided confronting China about its persecution of Uighurs despite bipartisan pressure, fearing such a move could harm a deal.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The United States and China are racing to clinch a historic economic treaty as early as next week that could drastically reshape relations between the world’s two largest economies. But as negotiations reach their final stages, the sensitive subject of human rights has been left conspicuously off the table.

headline.main: In Push for Trade Deal, Trump Administration Shelves Sanctions Over China’s Crackdown on Uighurs
headline.print_headline: Unspoken in Final Trade Talks:  China’s Internment of Muslims

docs.abstract: The Treasury secretary spoke to the chief financial officer of Walmart about steering its supply chain away from China.
docs.snippet: The Treasury secretary spoke to the chief financial officer of Walmart about steering its supply chain away from China.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Treasury Secretary Steven Mnuchin said on Wednesday that he was personally questioning some of America’s largest companies about their plans for weathering the Trump administration’s trade war with China, including encouraging firms to reorient their supply chains and source their products elsewhere.

headline.main: Mnuchin Presses Companies for Trade War Contingency Plans
headline.print_headline: Mnuchin Presses Retailers On Plans Amid Trade War

docs.abstract: A previously unreleased design concept made by the Bureau of Engraving and Printing in late 2016 reveals what a Harriet Tubman $20 bill might look like.
docs.snippet: A previously unreleased design concept made by the Bureau of Engraving and Printing in late 2016 reveals what a Harriet Tubman $20 bill might look like.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Extensive work was well underway on a new $20 bill bearing the image of Harriet Tubman when Treasury Secretary Steven Mnuchin announced last month that the design of the note would be delayed for technical reasons by six years and might not include the former slave and abolitionist.

headline.main: See a Design of the Harriet Tubman $20 Bill That Mnuchin Delayed
headline.print_headline: Unreal Sight of a Nearly Real $20 Bill
